A view of the recently renovated Rose Garden at the White House on August 22, 2020 in Washington, DC. WASHINGTON - The White House Rose Garden has been given a makeover. It took three weeks to spruce up the garden in the spirit of its original 1962 design. READ: Melania Trump to star in US coronavirus awareness ads The work has been completed just in time for First Lady Melania Trump's speech to the Republican National Convention on Tuesday night. She will speak from the garden, famous for its proximity to the Oval Office. White House officials say the renovations were funded by private donations, and have declined to reveal the cost.